The paper presents an approach for linking entities in queries using a rich set of features, such as context-matching, word embeddings, and relatedness among candidate entities. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories in computer science, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Databases (cs.DB). However, given that the focus is on entity linking for queries, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories.
